<ol>
  <li>If you donâ€™t need a legend see <a href="http://rolandtanglao.com/2016/07/31/p2-simplest-ggplot2-pie-chart-with-colors-as-bar-values/">Simplest ggplot2 Pie Chart using colours as literal bar values</a>.</li>
  <li>Changes from the legend-less version:
    <ol>
      <li>in the aes() change TO <code class="highlighter-rouge">fill=colour</code> FROM <code class="highlighter-rouge">fill=I(colour)</code></li>
      <li>add <code class="highlighter-rouge">p = p + scale_fill_manual(values=c("#8B7D7D" = "#8B7D7D", "#4C3F3F" = "#4C3F3F", "#716666" = "#716666"))</code> (iâ€™m sure you can automate this colour=colour kludgery that i manully typed!)</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
</ol>

